            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-3">6.3 Indicative nature and change management</h3>

            <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed mb-4">
              All infrastructure costs in this section are indicative estimates and are subject to change based on a number of factors, including (but not limited to):
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6 text-[#2D2D2D]">
              <li>Changes to a client's security requirements or posture, before or after deployment</li>
              <li>Growth in usage, scale, data volume or user concurrency beyond MVP-level assumptions</li>
              <li>Movement from MVP to MLP or Matured Product features that require additional or larger Azure resources</li>
              <li>Region selection (pricing assumes Australia East)</li>
              <li>Infrastructure provider (current architecture targets Microsoft Azure; alternative providers will have different pricing)</li>
              <li>Movement in Azure retail pricing</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="p-5 rounded-lg bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-[#1B2A4A] mb-2">BrightKeep commitment on cost change</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-[#2D2D2D]">
                Where any of the factors above changes the expected infrastructure cost (for an existing deployment, a planned deployment, or a future deployment), BrightKeep will advise as soon as is practical. The advice will include the affected resources, the indicative new monthly figure, and any architectural changes required to deliver the change. Implementation of architectural changes that fall outside Section 3.1 is scoped under a future development contract per Section 3.4, not under this contract.
